{"title_page": "Scotland GAA", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2017}}\n{{Infobox GAA county |\n county gaa = Scotland GAA|\n crest           = [[File:Scotland GAA logo.jpg|150px]] |\n irish = Albain  |\n province = [[Britain GAA|Britain]] |\n grounds = Clydebank Community Sport Hub, \n60 Dean Street, Clydebank \nG81 1RL|\n dominant sport = Gaelic football & Hurling and Camogie |\n pattern_la=_shoulder_stripes_white_stripes_alt|pattern_b=_collarwhite_horizontalwhite |pattern_ra=_shoulder_stripes_white_stripes_alt|pattern_so1 = __3_stripes_white|\n leftarm=182D69|body=182D69|rightarm=182D69 |shorts=|socks=182D69 |<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportsfile.com/id/RP0061864/|title=Sportsfile - Ireland v Scotland - Senior Men's Shinty International - RP0061864|first=|last=Sportsfile|publisher=|accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref>\n|}}\nThe Scotland Board of the [[Gaelic Athletic Association]] (GAA) or '''Scotland GAA''' ({{Lang-gd|Comann L\u00f9th-chleasach G\u00e0idheal na h-Alba}}) is one of the [[GAA county|county boards]] of the GAA outside Ireland, and is responsible for [[Gaelic games]] in Scotland. The county board is also responsible for the Scottish inter-county teams. The Board participates with [[London GAA|London]], [[Gloucestershire GAA|Gloucestershire]], [[Hertfordshire GAA|Hertfordshire]], [[Lancashire GAA|Lancashire]], [[Warwickshire GAA|Warwickshire]], and [[Yorkshire GAA|Yorkshire]] under the [[British GAA]].\n\n==List of Clubs==\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"background:#efefef\"\n!Club\n!\n!Colours\n!City\n|-\n|[[D\u00fan Deagh D\u00e1lriada|D\u00e1lriada]]\n|\n|{{Color box|#000000}}{{Color box|#FFFF00}}\n|[[Aberdeen]]/[[Dundee]]\n|-\n|[[D\u00fanedin Connolly GAC|D\u00fanedin Connollys]]\n|\n|{{Color box|#05B045}}{{Color box|#2244AA}}\n|[[Edinburgh]]\n|-\n|[[Glasgow Gaels GFC|Glaschu Gaels]]\n|\n|{{Color box|#FF0000}}{{Color box|#FFFFFF}}\n|[[Glasgow]]\n|-\n|[[Sands MacSwineys GFC|Sands MacSwineys]]\n|\n|{{Color box|#FFFFFF}}{{Color box|#10AA44}}\n|[[Coatbridge]]\n|-\n|[[T\u00edr Conaill Harps]]\n|\n|{{Color box|#10AA44}}{{Color box|#FFFF00}}\n|[[Glasgow]]\n|-\n|Ceann Creige Hurling and Camogie Club\n|\n|\n|Glasgow\n|}\n\n==Men's Championship Top winners==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n! style=\"background:silver;\" |\n! style=\"background:silver;\" | '''Team'''\n! style=\"background:silver;\" | '''Winner'''\n! style=\"background:silver;\" | '''Winning Years'''\n|-\n| 1\n| [[D\u00fanedin Connolly GAC|D\u00fanedin Connollys]]\n| 15\n| 1994, 2003, 2004, 2005, 2007, 2008, 2009, 2010, 2011, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018\n|-\n| 2\n| Mulroy Gaels\n| 5\n| 1989, 1995, 1997, 1998, 2000\n|-\n| 3\n| [[Glaschu Gaels]]\n| 3\n| 2002, 2006, 2019\n|-\n| 4\n| [[Sands McSwiney]]\n| 3\n| 1990, 1991, 1999\n|-\n| 5\n| St Patricks\n| 3\n| 1986, 1987, 1996\n|-\n| 6\n| [[T\u00edr Conaill Harps]]\n| 2\n| 2001, 2012\n|-\n| 7\n| [[Dundee Dalriada]]\n| 2\n| 1992, 1993\n|-\n| 8\n| Clan Na Gael\n| 1\n| 1985\n|-\n| 9\n| Beltane Shamrocks\n| 1\n| 1988\n|}\n\n==Roll of honour==\n===Senior Men's Championship===\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"background:#efefef\"\n! Year\n! Winner\n! Score\n! Runner-up\n! Date\n! Venue\n! Attendance\n! Winning margin (points){{ref label|A|A}}\n|-\n| 2019\n| [[Glasgow Gaels GFC|Glaschu Gaels]]\n| 0-14 - 2-04\n| [[D\u00fanedin Connolly GAC|D\u00fanedin Connollys]]\n| 5 October 2019\n| St. Ambrose High School, Coatbridge\n| Unknown\n| 4\n|-\n| 2018\n| [[D\u00fanedin Connolly GAC|D\u00fanedin Connollys]]\n| 1-08 - 3-09\n| [[Glasgow Gaels GFC|Glaschu Gaels]]\n| 29 September 2018\n| St. Ambrose High School, Coatbridge\n| Unknown\n|7<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.glasgowgaels.com/juniors-crowned-county-champions-seniors-fall-to-connollys/|title=Juniors Crowned County Champions; Seniors fall to Connollys|date=2018-09-30|website=Glasgow Gaels|language=en-GB|access